sections.text: Registration; requirements.To be a registered interior designer, an individual shall:(1) Apply to the State Treasurer in a form and manner prescribed by the State Treasurer;(2) Pay an application fee of not more than fifty dollars as determined by the State Treasurer; and(3) Satisfy the requirements for placement on the registry as provided in section 71-6105.SourceLaws 2024, LB16, ยง 17.
